<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro mhd_assert is defined as ((void)0). Therefore the statement mhd_assert(c->write_buffer_send_offset <= new_buf_size); compiles to a no-op ((void)0) that is executed but has no effect; removing it would not change program behaviour. This is dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
